    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-29T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="841"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d841">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/6–2954: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-29T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 29, 1954—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 544. Repeated information Paris 519,
                    Saigon 226. Paris and Saigon eyes only. Department limit distribution. <persName
                        corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> told me this afternoon that no progress
                    whatever in military talks with Viet Minh and does not expect any progress for
                    several days. He felt they were trying little war of nerves on French and
                    advised Paris he felt it important that French “stand firm”.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> have received report from <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> and Swiss Security officers <persName
                        corresp="#p_MVM1">Molotov</persName> is due return Geneva July 8.</p>
                <p>At recess, <persName corresp="#p_KVV1">Kuznetsov</persName> referred to press
                    reports I was being withdrawn from Geneva, saying he thought it “important” I
                    not leave. I jocularly told him not to necessarily believe everything he reads
                    in the press, but noted I had been absent from Prague since March.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JUA1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
